Henry Sallows Walsh was an Australian politician and businessman.
Walsh was born c. 1804 in Lewes, Sussex, and arrived at the then Colony of Victoria in 1849.Walsh was elected as member of the City of Melbourne council on 1 November 1858.Walsh was the Mayor of Melbourne from 1858 to 1859.Walsh died on 8 July 1877 in Hawthorn, Victoria.
